  "local_port": 46532,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "PAN Card: I lost my Aadhaar card. How can I get a second copy?",
  "response": "To get a replacement for your lost Aadhaar card, follow these steps:\n\n1. **Visit the UIDAI Website**: Go to the official website of the Unique Identification Authority of India (UIDAI) at [uidai.gov.in](https://uidai.gov.in).\n\n2. **Retrieve Your Enrolment ID (EID) or Aadhaar Number**: If you remember your Aadhaar number or EID, you can proceed directly. If not, you can retrieve it using your registered mobile number on the UIDAI website.\n\n3. **Request a Download**: \n   - On the UIDAI website, click on \"Download Aadhaar\".\n   - Enter your Aadhaar number or EID and the security code displayed on the screen.\n   - You will receive an OTP (One-Time Password) on your registered mobile number. Enter this OTP to proceed.\n   - Once verified, you can download your Aadhaar card in a PDF format.\n\n4. **Print Your Aadhaar Card**: After downloading the PDF, you can print a physical copy of your Aadhaar card.\n\n5. **Request a PVC Card (Optional)**: If you prefer a more durable card, you can order a PVC Aadhaar card from the UIDAI website for a nominal fee. This card will be delivered to your registered address.\n\n6. **Visit an Aadhaar Enrolment Center (Alternative Method)**:\n   - If you face issues with the online process, you can visit a nearby Aadhaar Enrolment Center.\n   - Fill out the Aadhaar update/correction form and submit it along with a fee (if applicable).\n   - You will receive your replacement Aadhaar card by post within a few weeks.\n\nRemember to keep your Aadhaar number and personal details secure during this process. If you encounter any issues, you can reach out to the UIDAI helpline for assistance.",
